+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017wmxvQe45EPyv593Bzy8ij","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete SSG Toolkit Codebase Exploration\n\nI have thoroughly explored the entire Static Site Generator toolkit codebase. Here's everything you need to implement the 8 plugins correctly:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts       (45 lines - all core interfaces)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts      (116 lines - build orchestration with DAG)\n│   │   ├── templates.ts   (42 lines - default and list templates)\n│   │   └── index.ts       (3 lines - exports)\n│   └── plugins/           (currently empty - needs 8 plugins)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts       (195 lines - 15 tests for core engine)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts    (90 lines - 8 tests)\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts  (107 lines - 9 tests)\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts (107 lines - 9 tests)\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts        (126 lines - 10 tests)\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts        (120 lines - 8 tests)\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts    (114 lines - 7 tests)\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts         (101 lines - 8 tests)\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts      (95 lines - 9 tests)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. CORE TYPES & INTERFACES\n\n**File: `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store (KEY FOR INTER-PLUGIN COMMUNICATION)\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**KEY INSIGHTS:**\n- Plugins communicate via `ctx.data` Map (shared data store)\n- `dependencies` array ensures topological ordering\n- Files flow through `transformContent` hooks sequentially in dependency order\n- `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild` hooks run for initialization and post-processing\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE ARCHITECTURE\n\n**File: `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` (116 lines)**\n\n**Core Methods:**\n\n1. **`registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)`** - adds plugin to engine\n2. **`registerTemplate(template: Template)`** - adds template\n3. **`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** - topological sort with cycle detection\n4. **`build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** - orchestrates entire build:\n   - Creates empty BuildContext\n   - Executes all `beforeBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Applies `transformContent` hooks to all files in dependency order (CRUCIAL: sequentially per plugin)\n   - Renders each file with appropriate template into `ctx.output`\n   - Executes all `afterBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Returns final BuildContext\n\n**Build Flow:**\n```\n1. beforeBuild phase (plugins in order)\n2. transformContent phase (all files through each plugin in order)\n3. Template rendering (each file rendered with its template)\n4. afterBuild phase (plugins in order)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. PLUGIN ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW\n\n**All plugins must be exported from files in `/workspace/src/plugins/`:**\n\nEach plugin module exports a factory function:\n```typescript\nexport function createXxxPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'xxx',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: ['dep1', 'dep2'],\n    hooks: {\n      beforeBuild?: (ctx) => { /* init logic */ },\n      transformContent?: (file, ctx) => { /* transform file */ },\n      afterBuild?: (ctx) => { /* finalization */ },\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Critical Points:**\n- Files import from `'../../src/plugins/xxx.js'` in tests (ESM with .js extensions)\n- Each plugin must implement only the hooks it needs\n- Use `ctx.data` to store and retrieve shared state\n- Dependencies must be declared for correct execution order\n\n---\n\n### 5. WAVE 1 PLUGINS (No Dependencies)\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext**\n\n**Factory:** `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n\n**Purpose:** Convert markdown to HTML with footnotes and admonitions\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Basic markdown:** Convert `# Hello` → `<h1>Hello</h1>`, `**bold**` → `<strong>bold</strong>`\n- **Footnotes:** Process `text[^1]` and `[^1]: Note` → renders as `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` with footnotes section at bottom\n- **Admonitions:** Convert markdown containers to divs:\n  - `:::note ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">...</div>`\n  - `:::warning ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">...</div>`\n  - `:::tip ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">...</div>`\n- **Preserve HTML:** If content is already HTML, don't double-convert\n- **Handle empty:** Empty content should not error\n\n**Hook:** `transformContent` (converts file.content from markdown to HTML)\n\n**Library:** Use `marked` npm package (already in dependencies)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Basic markdown with emphasis\n- Footnote syntax with link anchors\n- Footnote section rendering\n- Multiple admonition types\n- HTML preservation\n- Empty content\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 2: asset-pipeline**\n\n**Factory:** `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n\n**Purpose:** Rewrite relative asset URLs and generate manifest\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (9 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **URL Rewriting:**\n  - `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n  - `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n  - Absolute URLs (http/https/protocol) → unchanged\n  - Already rewritten `/assets/...` → unchanged\n\n- **Manifest Generation:**\n  - Store in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: [...] })`\n  - Track all extracted asset filenames\n  - Accumulate across multiple files\n\n- **Patterns to match:**\n  - `src=\"./...\"` in img tags\n  - `href=\"./...\"` in a tags (and other elements)\n  - Only relative paths starting with `./`\n\n**Hook:** `transformContent` (rewrites URLs in file.content)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Image URL rewriting\n- Link URL rewriting\n- Absolute URL preservation\n- Manifest creation and accumulation\n- Multiple assets in one file\n- No assets in file\n- Already-rewritten URL skip\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 3: syntax-highlight**\n\n**Factory:** `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n\n**Purpose:** Add language classes and attributes to code blocks\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (9 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Code Block Detection:** Find `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">...</code></pre>` patterns\n- **Transformation:**\n  - Add `highlighted` class to the code element: `class=\"language-XXX highlighted\"`\n  - Add `data-language=\"XXX\"` attribute to the pre element\n  - Extract language from `language-XXX` class\n\n- **Rules:**\n  - Only process blocks WITH `language-*` class\n  - Leave plain `<code>` blocks in inline content untouched\n  - Preserve code block content exactly\n\n**Hook:** `transformContent` (adds classes/attributes to code blocks)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Language class addition\n- data-language attribute on pre\n- Multiple blocks in one file\n- Code blocks without language specified (no modification)\n- Inline code untouched\n- Empty code blocks handled\n- Content preservation\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 4: taxonomy**\n\n**Factory:** `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n\n**Purpose:** Build tag/category index and generate tag listing pages\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (10 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **beforeBuild Hook:**\n  - Scan all `ctx.files` for tags\n  - Create Map: `tag → [files with that tag]`\n  - Normalize tags to lowercase\n  - Store in `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', tagMap)`\n\n- **afterBuild Hook:**\n  - For each tag, generate an HTML page:\n    - Path: `tags/{tag}.html` \n    - Content: Simple list of files with that tag (show title/slug)\n    - Store in `ctx.output`\n\n- **Edge Cases:**\n  - Files with no tags (skip)\n  - Normalize case: 'JavaScript' + 'JAVASCRIPT' → 1 entry 'javascript'\n  - Empty file list (no output)\n\n**Hooks:** `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Tag index building\n- Tag page generation\n- Case normalization\n- Multiple tags per file\n- Files without tags\n- Empty file list\n\n---\n\n### 6. WAVE 2 PLUGINS (Depend on Wave 1)\n\n#### **Plugin 5: rss-feed**\n\n**Factory:** `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate RSS 2.0 feed\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Generate `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n\n- **XML Structure:**\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n  <rss version=\"2.0\">\n    <channel>\n      <title>{config.title}</title>\n      <link>{config.baseUrl}</link>\n      <item>\n        <title>{file.title}</title>\n        <link>{config.baseUrl}/{file.slug}.html</link>\n        <description><![CDATA[{file.content}]]></description>\n        <pubDate>{file.date}</pubDate>\n        <category>{tag}</category>  <!-- for each tag -->\n      </item>\n    </channel>\n  </rss>\n  ```\n\n- **Content:** Feed items contain HTML content (from markdown-ext transform)\n\n- **Categories:** Extract from taxonomy-tags map, add `<category>` elements for matching files\n\n- **Sorting:** Items sorted by date, newest first\n\n- **Date Handling:** Files without dates should not show `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild` (generates feed after all content ready)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Valid RSS 2.0 XML structure\n- HTML content in CDATA\n- Categories from taxonomy\n- Channel title from config\n- Newest-first sorting\n- Missing dates handled\n- baseUrl used in links\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 6: search-index**\n\n**Factory:** `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate searchable index JSON\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Generate `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n\n- **Index Format:** Array of objects:\n  ```json\n  [\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"post-slug\",\n      \"title\": \"Post Title\",\n      \"content\": \"plain text content (no HTML tags)\",\n      \"tags\": [\"optional\", \"tags\"]\n    }\n  ]\n  ```\n\n- **Content Processing:**\n  - Strip all HTML tags from `file.content`\n  - Include code block content (text within `<code>` tags)\n  - Result is plain searchable text\n\n- **Tags:** Include if present in file\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild` (generates index after all content ready)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- JSON validity\n- HTML tag stripping\n- Code block inclusion\n- Title/slug/content in output\n- Tags in output\n- Empty file list (empty array)\n- Multiple files\n\n---\n\n### 7. WAVE 3 PLUGINS (Depend on Wave 2)\n\n#### **Plugin 7: sitemap**\n\n**Factory:** `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate XML sitemap for search engines\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Generate `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n\n- **XML Structure:**\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n  <urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n    <url>\n      <loc>https://example.com/path.html</loc>\n    </url>\n  </urlset>\n  ```\n\n- **URLs Included:**\n  - All content pages from `ctx.output` (HTML files)\n  - All tag pages from taxonomy (from `taxonomy-tags` in `ctx.data`)\n  - feed.xml if present\n\n- **URL Construction:** `{config.baseUrl}/{path}`\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild` (generates sitemap after all content ready)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Valid XML structure\n- Content page URLs\n- Tag page URLs from taxonomy\n- Feed URL inclusion\n- baseUrl usage\n- No tag pages when taxonomy empty\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 8: dev-server**\n\n**Factory:** `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate development server configuration\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (9 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Store in `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', {...})`\n\n- **Config Structure:**\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: 3000,\n    routes: [\n      { path: \"/page.html\", handler: \"static\" },\n      { path: \"/assets/image.png\", handler: \"asset\" }\n    ],\n    assetPaths: [\"image.png\", \"style.css\"],\n    searchIndexPath: \"/search-index.json\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Routes:**\n  - Content routes: one per file in `ctx.output` (handler: \"static\")\n  - Asset routes: one per asset from `asset-manifest` (handler: \"asset\")\n\n- **Asset Paths:** From `asset-manifest.assets` in `ctx.data` (if present)\n\n- **Search Index Path:** \"/search-index.json\" if present in `ctx.output`\n\n- **Default Port:** 3000\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild`\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Config storage in ctx.data\n- Port setting\n- Asset routes from asset-pipeline\n- Search index path detection\n- Content routes from output\n- Default port 3000\n- Graceful handling of missing asset-pipeline\n\n---\n\n### 8. BUILD ORDER VERIFICATION\n\nWith all 8 plugins registered, the engine will topologically sort them as:\n\n```\nWave 1 (no deps, any order):\n  1. markdown-ext\n  2. asset-pipeline\n  3. syntax-highlight\n  4. taxonomy\n\nWave 2:\n  5. rss-feed        (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n  6. search-index    (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\nWave 3:\n  7. sitemap         (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n  8. dev-server      (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n```\n\n**Actual order may vary within each wave, but:**\n- All Wave 1 plugins before Wave 2\n- All Wave 2 plugins before Wave 3\n- Dependencies always satisfied\n\n---\n\n### 9. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n**`package.json`** (28 lines):\n- Main: `dist/core/index.js`\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint`, `test` (vitest run)\n- Type: `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- Dependencies: `marked`, `express`, `@types/marked`, `@types/express`\n- DevDependencies: TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint\n\n**`tsconfig.json`** (14 lines):\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16 (ESM support)\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`** (8 lines):\n- Global test utilities\n- 10 second timeout\n\n**`.eslintrc.cjs`** (19 lines):\n- TypeScript parser\n- Recommended + TypeScript plugin\n- Rule: Unused vars OK if prefixed with `_`\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY TESTING PATTERNS\n\nEach plugin test file:\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { createXxxPlugin } from '../../src/plugins/xxx.js';\n\n// Helper functions\nfunction makeCtx(): BuildContext { /* ... */ }\nfunction makeFile(overrides): ContentFile { /* ... */ }\n\ndescribe('xxx plugin', () => {\n  const plugin = createXxxPlugin();\n  \n  it('test name', async () => {\n    const result = await plugin.hooks.hookName!(input, ctx);\n    expect(result).toBe(expected);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n1. **ESM Imports:** Use `.js` extensions in import paths (e.g., `./engine.js`)\n2. **Shared State:** `ctx.data` is the ONLY communication between plugins\n3. **Type Safety:** All code must pass TypeScript strict mode\n4. **File Transformation:** Files modified in `transformContent` persist through rest of pipeline\n5. **Output vs Assets:** `ctx.output` for text (HTML/XML/JSON), `ctx.assets` for binary\n6. **HTML Parsing:** May need simple regex patterns for HTML manipulation (no external DOM parser required)\n7. **Error Handling:** Tests don't check errors, but implementations should be robust\n8. **Async/Await:** Hooks can be async; engine awaits them\n9. **Dependency Order:** Engine handles via `resolvePluginOrder()` - just declare your dependencies correctly\n10. **No Plugin Lookup:** Plugins don't call each other directly; they use `ctx.data` for shared state\n\n---\n\n### 12. CORE TEST SUITE (15 tests)\n\nFile: `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` - These MUST continue to pass:\n- Plugin registration\n- Template registration\n- Default and list template rendering\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Dependency resolution and circular detection\n- Multiple plugin chaining in order\n- Shared data store access\n- Metadata preservation\n- Empty file handling\n\nYou now have complete architectural understanding of the toolkit. The plugins communicate through the `BuildContext.data` Map, execute in dependency order, and each one transforms files or produces output/assets during the build pipeline."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad90397 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37414\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 64458</usage>"}]}]},"pare