lain text content (no HTML tags)\",\n      \"tags\": [\"optional\", \"tags\"]\n    }\n  ]\n  ```\n\n- **Content Processing:**\n  - Strip all HTML tags from `file.content`\n  - Include code block content (text within `<code>` tags)\n  - Result is plain searchable text\n\n- **Tags:** Include if present in file\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild` (generates index after all content ready)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- JSON validity\n- HTML tag stripping\n- Code block inclusion\n- Title/slug/content in output\n- Tags in output\n- Empty file list (empty array)\n- Multiple files\n\n---\n\n### 7. WAVE 3 PLUGINS (Depend on Wave 2)\n\n#### **Plugin 7: sitemap**\n\n**Factory:** `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate XML sitemap for search engines\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Generate `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n\n- **XML Structure:**\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n  <urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n    <url>\n      <loc>https://example.com/path.html</loc>\n    </url>\n  </urlset>\n  ```\n\n- **URLs Included:**\n  - All content pages from `ctx.output` (HTML files)\n  - All tag pages from taxonomy (from `taxonomy-tags` in `ctx.data`)\n  - feed.xml if present\n\n- **URL Construction:** `{config.baseUrl}/{path}`\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild` (generates sitemap after all content ready)\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Valid XML structure\n- Content page URLs\n- Tag page URLs from taxonomy\n- Feed URL inclusion\n- baseUrl usage\n- No tag pages when taxonomy empty\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 8: dev-server**\n\n**Factory:** `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies:** `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\n**Purpose:** Generate development server configuration\n\n**Tests:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (9 tests)\n\n**Required Behavior:**\n\n- **Output:** Store in `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', {...})`\n\n- **Config Structure:**\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: 3000,\n    routes: [\n      { path: \"/page.html\", handler: \"static\" },\n      { path: \"/assets/image.png\", handler: \"asset\" }\n    ],\n    assetPaths: [\"image.png\", \"style.css\"],\n    searchIndexPath: \"/search-index.json\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Routes:**\n  - Content routes: one per file in `ctx.output` (handler: \"static\")\n  - Asset routes: one per asset from `asset-manifest` (handler: \"asset\")\n\n- **Asset Paths:** From `asset-manifest.assets` in `ctx.data` (if present)\n\n- **Search Index Path:** \"/search-index.json\" if present in `ctx.output`\n\n- **Default Port:** 3000\n\n**Hook:** `afterBuild`\n\n**Key Test Cases:**\n- Config storage in ctx.data\n- Port setting\n- Asset routes from asset-pipeline\n- Search index path detection\n- Content routes from output\n- Default port 3000\n- Graceful handling of missing asset-pipeline\n\n---\n\n### 8. BUILD ORDER VERIFICATION\n\nWith all 8 plugins registered, the engine will topologically sort them as:\n\n```\nWave 1 (no deps, any order):\n  1. markdown-ext\n  2. asset-pipeline\n  3. syntax-highlight\n  4. taxonomy\n\nWave 2:\n  5. rss-feed        (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n  6. search-index    (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\nWave 3:\n  7. sitemap         (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n  8. dev-server      (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n```\n\n**Actual order may vary within each wave, but:**\n- All Wave 1 plugins before Wave 2\n- All Wave 2 plugins before Wave 3\n- Dependencies always satisfied\n\n---\n\n### 9. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n**`package.json`** (28 lines):\n- Main: `dist/core/index.js`\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint`, `test` (vitest run)\n- Type: `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- Dependencies: `marked`, `express`, `@types/marked`, `@types/express`\n- DevDependencies: TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint\n\n**`tsconfig.json`** (14 lines):\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16 (ESM support)\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`** (8 lines):\n- Global test utilities\n- 10 second timeout\n\n**`.eslintrc.cjs`** (19 lines):\n- TypeScript parser\n- Recommended + TypeScript plugin\n- Rule: Unused vars OK if prefixed with `_`\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY TESTING PATTERNS\n\nEach plugin test file:\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { createXxxPlugin } from '../../src/plugins/xxx.js';\n\n// Helper functions\nfunction makeCtx(): BuildContext { /* ... */ }\nfunction makeFile(overrides): ContentFile { /* ... */ }\n\ndescribe('xxx plugin', () => {\n  const plugin = createXxxPlugin();\n  \n  it('test name', async () => {\n    const result = await plugin.hooks.hookName!(input, ctx);\n    expect(result).toBe(expected);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n1. **ESM Imports:** Use `.js` extensions in import paths (e.g., `./engine.js`)\n2. **Shared State:** `ctx.data` is the ONLY communication between plugins\n3. **Type Safety:** All code must pass TypeScript strict mode\n4. **File Transformation:** Files modified in `transformContent` persist through rest of pipeline\n5. **Output vs Assets:** `ctx.output` for text (HTML/XML/JSON), `ctx.assets` for binary\n6. **HTML Parsing:** May need simple regex patterns for HTML manipulation (no external DOM parser required)\n7. **Error Handling:** Tests don't check errors, but implementations should be robust\n8. **Async/Await:** Hooks can be async; engine awaits them\n9. **Dependency Order:** Engine handles via `resolvePluginOrder()` - just declare your dependencies correctly\n10. **No Plugin Lookup:** Plugins don't call each other directly; they use `ctx.data` for shared state\n\n---\n\n### 12. CORE TEST SUITE (15 tests)\n\nFile: `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` - These MUST continue to pass:\n- Plugin registration\n- Template registration\n- Default and list template rendering\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Dependency resolution and circular detection\n- Multiple plugin chaining in order\n- Shared data store access\n- Metadata preservation\n- Empty file handling\n\nYou now have complete architectural understanding of the toolkit. The plugins communicate through the `BuildContext.data` Map, execute in dependency order, and each one transforms files or produces output/assets during the build pipeline."}],"totalDurationMs":64458,"totalTokens":37414,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":221,"cache_read_input_tokens":32124,"output_tokens":5066,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":221,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
